profit calculation question.

00:16:04.485 --> 00:16:10.425
A shopkeeper buys an article for 450
rupees and sells it for 540 rupees.

00:16:10.785 --> 00:16:12.959
What is the profit percentage options?

00:16:13.564 --> 00:16:14.855
A 15%.

00:16:15.185 --> 00:16:18.425
B, 20% C, 25%.

00:16:18.575 --> 00:16:22.955
D 10% understand the question
before moving to explanation.

00:16:23.285 --> 00:16:24.814
Step-by-step solution.

00:16:25.055 --> 00:16:29.915
Step one, first, identify the
cost, price, CP and selling price.

00:16:29.915 --> 00:16:35.675
SP here CP is 450 Rupees
and SP is 540 rupees.

00:16:35.855 --> 00:16:36.665
Easy peasy.

00:16:36.875 --> 00:16:37.595
Step two.

00:16:37.835 --> 00:16:39.575
Now, calculate the profit.

00:16:39.875 --> 00:16:46.535
Profit as we know, is SP minus
cp, so 540 rupees minus 450

00:16:46.535 --> 00:16:48.395
rupees gives us 90 rupees.

00:16:48.545 --> 00:16:49.835
That's the profit amount.

00:16:50.045 --> 00:16:53.375
Step three, finally calculate
the profit percentage.

00:16:53.675 --> 00:16:58.025
Remember the formula profit
percentage equals profit divided by

00:16:58.025 --> 00:17:04.085
CP multiplied by a hundred, so 90
divided by 450 multiplied by a hundred.

00:17:04.615 --> 00:17:09.775
This simplifies to one divided by five,
multiplied by a hundred, which is 20%.

00:17:10.015 --> 00:17:12.895
So the correct answer is B 20%.

00:17:13.075 --> 00:17:14.695
C told you it's simple.

00:17:15.055 --> 00:17:17.815
Example, two discount and marked price.

00:17:18.085 --> 00:17:18.655
Question.

00:17:18.955 --> 00:17:21.625
A shirt is marked at 1,200 rupees.

00:17:21.944 --> 00:17:25.754
The shopkeeper offers a discount
of 15% on the marked price.

00:17:26.085 --> 00:17:28.665
What is the selling price
of the shirt options?

00:17:29.205 --> 00:17:35.115
A 1020 B 1000 C 900 D 1050.

00:17:35.475 --> 00:17:38.115
Understand the question
before moving to explanation.

00:17:38.435 --> 00:17:39.905
Step-by-step solution.

00:17:40.115 --> 00:17:42.725
Step one, identify the marked price.

00:17:42.754 --> 00:17:44.645
MP and discount percentage.

00:17:44.945 --> 00:17:49.264
MP is 1,200 rupees and
discount percent is 15%.

00:17:49.564 --> 00:17:51.995
This is the tag price and
the discount, my friend.

00:17:52.205 --> 00:17:54.635
Step two, calculate the discount amount.

00:17:54.935 --> 00:18:01.235
Discount is 15% of the marked price, so 15
divided by a hundred, multiplied by 1200.

00:18:01.534 --> 00:18:06.125
This calculates to 15 multiplied
by 12, which is 180 rupees.

00:18:06.304 --> 00:18:07.325
That's your saving.

00:18:07.565 --> 00:18:08.285
Step three.

00:18:08.525 --> 00:18:10.475
Now calculate the selling price.

00:18:10.715 --> 00:18:16.385
SP is simply the marked price minus
the discount, so 1,200 rupees minus

00:18:16.385 --> 00:18:19.925
180 rupees, which gives us 1020 rupees.

00:18:20.105 --> 00:18:21.635
This is what you actually pay.

00:18:21.905 --> 00:18:25.835
Alternatively, using the direct
formula, which is sometimes faster.

00:18:26.165 --> 00:18:31.325
SP equals MP multiplied by a hundred minus
discount percent divided by a hundred.

00:18:31.540 --> 00:18:36.760
So 1,200 multiplied by a hundred,
minus 15 divided by a hundred.

00:18:37.030 --> 00:18:42.429
This becomes 1,200, multiplied by
85 divided by a hundred, which is 12

00:18:42.429 --> 00:18:45.699
multiplied by 85, giving you 1020 rupees.

00:18:45.850 --> 00:18:51.310
Both ways lead to the same answer, so
the correct answer is a 1020 rupees.

